1. *Politika* je jedna od najstarijih novina u Srbiji. (Politics is one of the oldest newspapers in Serbia.)
2. Ona se bavi *politikom* i ima značajnu ulogu u vladi. (She deals with politics and has a significant role in the government.)
3. Potrebno je da se uskladimo sa *politikom* Evropske Unije. (We need to align ourselves with the policies of the European Union.)
4. Izjava predsednika stranke izazvala je veliki interes u medijima i izazvala polemiku o *politici*. (The statement by the party leader caused a lot of interest in the media and sparked a debate about politics.)
5. *Politikom* upravlja vlada, a ne pojedinci. (Politics is managed by the government, not individuals.)
6. U Srbiji se *politika* često koristi kao tema raznih javnih debata i tribina. (In Serbia, politics is often used as a topic of various public debates and forums.)
7. Bivši predsednik je optužen za zloupotrebu *politike* u svrhu lične promocije. (The former president was accused of misusing politics for personal promotion.)
8. *Politiku* ne bi smeli da se mešaju sa poslovnim interesima. (Politics should not be mixed with business interests.)
9. *Politika* je značajan faktor u oblikovanju spoljne politike države. (Politics is a significant factor in shaping the foreign policy of the country.)
10. On se bavi *politikom* i smatra da može da promeni stvari u zemlji. (He is involved in politics and believes he can change things in the country.)